race.comment: ANGELIC RISE (5) had her share of market support on debut in Listed company at Flemington, striking tough conditions after opening quite short. She battled home okay there and firmer ground should suit far better for this speedy type. If she's come through the run well, she should go close. KO PHANGAN (2) is a colt by Ole Kirk on debut for the Busuttin & Young stable. He's jumped out well and notably gets Mark Zahra aboard from a good gate. Expecting him to take plenty of beating. OMAN (7) is a filly by Capitalist on debut for the formidable Begg/Childs combination. She's trialled well enough and draws the inside gate. Respecting. ASTILLA (6) is a Hanseatic filly on debut for the Freedman yard who has won a jumpout for a renowned 2yo yard, keep safe if the money comes. ALMOST AN ANGEL (4) is a So You Think filly on debut who has jumped out well, she can be strong late.
